HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 44
BY REPRESENTATIVE TURNER
A RESOLUTION
To commend Malcolm "Coldblooded" Lee on being named Louisiana Outstanding Log
Truck Driver of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Malcolm "Coldblooded" Lee for his
dedication to safe and efficient log truck driving practices in northeast Louisiana and to
commend him on being named Louisiana Outstanding Log Truck Driver of the Year; and
WHEREAS, log truck drivers move timber from forest land to mills for processing
and are a vital part of the Louisiana logging industry; and
WHEREAS, log truck drivers spend countless hours on the road, navigating through
rural communities, school zones, and congested roadways, and they are always focused on
recognizing the potential for accidents and ensuring the safety of the public and their
truckloads and equipment; and
WHEREAS, without log truck drivers, the logging industry would not exist, and the
forests of Louisiana would become overgrown and unproductive; log truck drivers also
contribute significantly to local economies by purchasing parts, fuel, and lubricants; they
also support charitable causes and community needs; and
WHEREAS, log truck drivers face a variety of day-to-day issues, including inclimate
weather, a volatile market, and equipment failures; these problems often result in long work
hours, and drivers rely on their faith and family to overcome them; and
WHEREAS, Malcolm "Coldblooded" Lee was selected by the Louisiana Logging
Council to represent all that is good about log truck drivers, and his professional reputation
distinguishes him as one of the state's best log truck owner-operators.
